{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/acpi/video_detect.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.9,
  "reasoning": "The bug is that the Acer TravelMate 5735Z is missing from the video_detect_dmi_table in drivers/acpi/video_detect.c. The acpi_video_get_backlight_type() function uses this DMI table to determine which backlight interface to use. Without an entry for this machine, the autodetect logic falls through to acpi_backlight_video (since the machine has ACPI video capability but is not a Win8 BIOS). However, the machine requires acpi_backlight_native to work correctly, as evidenced by the bug report showing that booting with acpi_backlight=native fixes brightness control. The fix is to add a video_detect_force_native DMI entry for the Acer TravelMate 5735Z (sys_vendor=Acer, product_name=TravelMate 5735Z) in the video_detect_dmi_table data structure."
}

